#import "/formatting.typ": *
#import "/shared-data.typ": *

#show: recipe.with(
  title: "Sourdough Milk Bread",
  description: [
    This bread is Soft. See the original recipe here: #link(
      "https://www.butterforall.com/traditional-cooking-traditional-living/sourdough-milk-bread/",
    )
  ],
)[
  Equipment:
  - 9"x5" loaf pan #footnote[Cast iron not recommended. I like my #url("Pullman loaf pan")
      from the King Arthur Baking Company.]

  Ingredients:
  - 125g active sourdough starter, 100% hydration #aside[1/2 cup]
  - 300g flour #footnote[
      A majority of the flour should be all-purpose or bread flour. Highly recommend up to
      75 grams (25%) of einkorn flour for flavor. Still experimenting with potato flour;
      so far, it seems like it produces softer but more sour bread, and a very low rise
      (#sym.arrow a need to use more flour).
    ] #aside[1 cup]
  - 20g honey #aside[2 tbsp.]
  - 210g milk milk #aside[5/6 cup]
  - 8g salt #aside[1 1/4 tsp.]

  *Yields 1 loaf.*
]

+ MIX ingredients until combined.
+ COVER and proof overnight.#footnote[Stretch & folds immediately following this step are
    optional: if you don't do any stretch and folds, the dough will break in the morning,
    but it may (or may not) contribute to a softer texture.] #pause[8-16 hr.]
+ REST. #pause[5 min.]
+ PREHEAT oven to 200°C. #aside[400°F]
+ TWICE:~
  + FLATTEN into thick rectangle, short side closest to you. Fold top third down and
    remaining third up.
  + REST on seam. #pause[5 min.]
+ MOVE dough to greased loaf pan.
+ REST until doubled. #pause[1-8 hr.]
+ SCORE and lightly spray with water.
+ BAKE covered. #pause[35-40 min.]
+ COOL outside of oven. #pause[5 min.]
+ COOL directly on wire racks. #pause[30 min.]
